finaliseEpoch().details: In addition to new nodes, it copies nodes from NEXT epoch

returns._0: Array of Node structs representing the current committee

params.baseFee: The base fee to be used when a validator has no recent vote.

returns._0: uint The gas fee to be used.
Array of Node structs representing the next epoch's committee

params.nodeAddress: Address of the node to check

returns._0: True if the node is registered, false otherwise

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

params.nodeAddress: The address of the node to check

returns._0: The total stake-weighted votes the node has received

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

params.initialMaxNodes: Maximum number of nodes in the committee
params.upgrader: Address that will have upgrade rights

joinCommittee(address,uint256,(bytes,byt.details: Adds the node to the FUTURE epoch if not already registered

params.nodeAddress: Address of the node joining the committee
params.publicKeys: Public keys associated with the node

leaveCommittee(address).details: Removes the node from future epochs

params.rewardsPayedToContract: Amount of rewards to be distributed

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

burnFeePercentage().notice: Returns the percentage of fees that will be burned

getCurrentEpochCommittee().notice: Gets the current epoch's committee members

getCurrentGasPrice(uint256).notice: Gets the current gas price using the gas price votes from all validators         in the current epoch.

getFinalisedNodes().notice: Returns the list of nodes in the finalized FUTURE epoch

getNextEpochCommittee().notice: Returns the list of nodes in the NEXT epoch

getRegisteredNode(address).notice: Gets whether a node is currently registered in the committee

getWarnedNodeWeight(address).notice: Returns the stake-weighted votes a node has received

initialize(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Initializes the contract with initial parameters

joinCommittee(address,uint256,(bytes,byt.notice: Allows a new node to join the committee

leaveCommittee(address).notice: Allows a node to leave the committee

maxNodes().notice: Returns the maximum number of nodes allowed in the committee

moveToNextEpoch(uint256).notice: Moves the epochs forward and processes rewards

nodeCommitteeStaking().notice: Returns the address of the staking contract

setBurnFeePercentage(uint256).notice: Updates the percentage of fees to be burned

setNodeCommitteeStaking(address).notice: Updates the address of the node committee staking contract

setNodeGasPriceVote(uint256).notice: Sets the latest gas price vote for the sender. This will accept votes for any address         (as the sender pays the gas).
